            "title" : "The ground of Alexandria",
            "content_html" : "<h3 id=\"ambiance\">Ambiance:</h3>\n<p>Hosted in what it seems to be an old warehouse complex covered with exotic plants, the ground offer a magical place to enjoy a brunch. <code>The original idea was to turn this industrial concrete car park into an urban sanctuary, to create a welcoming space to bring people together</code>. Few events are organized over the year, check their <a href=\"https://thegrounds.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\">website</a> for more.</p>\n<h3 id=\"cuisine\">Cuisine:</h3>\n<p>The different types of market stand and the coffee shop does propose a wide range of food, from local honey producer to pasta and burger. </p>\n<h3 id=\"pricing\">Pricing:</h3>\n<p>The pricing varies in function of what stand you are buying from, you can find a  meal for an average of $20. For more information about their pricing and menu details you can check their <a href=\"https://thegrounds.com.au/food-drink/\" target=\"_blank\">shop details</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"service\">Service:</h3>\n<p>It is often quite hard to find a place to sit, particularly in summer, and it is the principal down point. It is easily balance with the welcoming staff always happy to help you choose what to eat. The market cover under a nearby building is the occasion to try new clothes and accessories.</p>\n<h3 id=\"location\">Location:</h3>\n<p>It is quite hard to find the ground the first time. From Sydney Park it is a 20min walk before reaching the entrance of the complex. For the full location you can check <a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Grounds+of+Alexandria/@-33.910825,151.1943905,15z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x0:0xaf0cfe2766ccbc4a!8m2!3d-33.910825!4d151.1943905\" target=\"_blank\">google maps</a>. If you don't feel the motivation to lose yourself in Alexandria, you should, <a href=\"https://thegroundscity.com.au/our-first-birthday/\" target=\"_blank\">the ground of the city</a> is also available in Town Hall.</p>",
