            "title" : "Pancake on the rock",
            "content_html" : "<h3 id=\"ambiance\">Ambiance:</h3>\n<p>Pancake on the Rock is the place to go if you like pancakes. The first restaurant opened on Hickson Road, close to circular quay, in 1975. The place itself, aside of its location is not exceptional. Big televisions and projector display 90's music, a jukebox will let you choose. But the general feeling of the place is the one of an American dine in.\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/WJLtnfk.jpg\" alt=\"pancake at the rock\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"cuisine\">Cuisine:</h3>\n<p>As you surely guessed it by now, the restaurant serves an extensive range of pancake. From what we've seen the pancake base is the same, but the topping are limitless. Ice cream, berry jam, maple syrup you name it. Check their menu to see all their choices. But the restaurant also offers a wide variety of steak and other American meals. We didn't find the willpower to try something else than pancakes, but the meal we've seen looks large and tasty. On a side note, don't trust the pancake on their appearance, they are massive. Being able to eat 3 of them is an exploit to me.</p>\n<h3 id=\"pricing\">Pricing:</h3>\n<p>The pancakes are the same price than any regular meal, count between $10 and $20. The price depend with the amount of pancake and its topping. Other types of meals are usually around $20 with the exception of the beef ribs at $36. Check their <a href=\"https://www.pancakesontherocks.com.au/menu/\" target=\"_blank\">menu</a> for more. Pancake on the rock also sells <a href=\"https://www.pancakesontherocks.com.au/merchandise/\" target=\"_blank\">merchandising</a> including shirt and pancake mix.</p>\n<h3 id=\"service\">Service:</h3>\n<p>If you visit the Rock's restaurant, we recommend to come outside of peak hour, as the place gets easily crowded. But don't get fooled by it, the place is huge and the kitchen too, once sited the waiting is usually short. You can can judge the waiting list from the queue extending from the entrance. There are plenty of waiters to make sure you won't be waiting to place your order.</p>\n<h3 id=\"location\">Location:</h3>\n<p>We've only tried their restaurant on the Rock. It's 15 minutes walk from Circular Quay station. If you decide to get there on a Saturday, you will be able to enjoy the Rock Market at its doorstep. There is few location around Sydney, you can find them all on <a href=\"https://www.pancakesontherocks.com.au/location/\" target=\"_blank\">their website</a>. If you are curious to see something different than the  CBD, you can have a try at the North-Strathfield one. This second restaurant is built in the old Arnotts biscuit factory which is a nice area to visit.</p>",
