            "title" : "The Baxter inn",
            "content_html" : "<h3 id=\"ambiance\">Ambiance:</h3>\n<p>Hidden only few hundred meters away from Town hall the Baxter Inn is a must do. \nOnce you find its entrance, you can start to appreciate the prohibition style of its place. Candles are dripping forming piles of wax, old carpet and whiskey barrels on a remote room perfect the style. The place is often crowded, especially after work hours. You might quite often end up standing and yelling to have any sort of conversation, but this is the price to pay to access this original bar. Their <a href=\"http://thebaxterinn.com\" target=\"_blank\">website</a> can always help event if it's mostly empty.</p>\n<h3 id=\"selection\">Selection:</h3>\n<p>The place is mostly famous for its large selection of whisky. If you are heading that way we recommend for you to have a conversation with the bartender, they will happily direct you with the best choice following your taste and budget. The place also offers a reduced selection of beer and wine if your taste isn't toward whisky.</p>\n<h3 id=\"pricing\">Pricing:</h3>\n<p>The prices are reasonable, count around $8 for a draft beer and $20 for a good whiskey. The price can go much higher if you planning to buy a good bottle of whiskey.</p>\n<h3 id=\"location\">Location:</h3>\n<p>Following the <a href=\"https://www.google.com.au/maps/place/The+Baxter+Inn/@-33.8697229,151.2034453,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x6b12ae3f3d3843d7:0x7a711a8708afea31!8m2!3d-33.8697229!4d151.205634\" target=\"_blank\">map</a> you realize than this bar, is only a 5 minutes walk to Town hall. But to actually find the entrance, you need to enter the inside courtyard of a building. Once inside you will see one bar, which isn't the Baxter inn, take your right in the direction of the bin, on the far end you will see a security guard. Then you can walk down the few stairs before opening the door leading to the place.</p>",
