            "title" : "Holey Moley",
            "content_html" : "<h3 id=\"ambiance\">Ambiance</h3>\n<p>Holy Moley is a bit of an outsider in our lists. The place isn't the type of bar you couldn't find without the help of a resident. We decided to keep it because of its non-conventional style. Holey Moley is built around a mini-golf court. And that is a pretty entertaining activity while having a drink. We particularly like the pop culture reference around each hole. Don't expect any serious golfing, but certain holes are challenging in their own way. Try to hit the ball through a rolling motorbike wheel, you'll see. The place also offers a service of karaoke. We did not tru it, there are plenty of other options around the CBD. We'd love to hear from you if you had the chance to try it.</p>\n<h3 id=\"selection\">Selection</h3>\n<p>The selection of food and alcohol is quite classic. It never meant to be the main attraction of the bar. There are few choices of draft beers, cocktails, wine. You can also expect some greasy burger, pizza and hot dog, if you are getting hungry. 3 choices of golf course are available, a 9 holes, an 18 holes and a 27 holes. The menu and golf course differ from locations. As for example the 27 holes is only available in Darlinghurst. You can get there without booking, but they have a very limited number of walk-ins available. We advise booking in advance. Their <a href=\"https://www.holeymoley.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\">website</a> gives detailed their choices of foods and drinks and allows you to book a session. </p>\n<h3 id=\"pricing\">Pricing</h3>\n<p>The food and drink pricing are quite common in front of other bar in the city. An average of $16 for a cocktail and $9 for a wine glass or a beer. Pizza, burgers and hot dog pricing vary between $13 to $20. Playing the golf is another cost, count $18 for a 9 holes, $34 a 18 holes and $44 for the 27th one. The karaoke room in $100 share between the group.</p>\n<h3 id=\"location\">Location</h3>\n<p>There is 2 Holey Moley in Sydney, the first one is in <a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Holey+Moley/@-33.8995368,151.1755692,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x6b12b036d1f01e1d:0x709e8913f0c5d999!8m2!3d-33.8995368!4d151.1777579\" target=\"_blank\">Newtown</a>, 10 minutes away from the train station. From there walk down king street another 5 minutes to find it. The second place is in <a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Holey+Moley+Golf+Club+Darlinghurst/@-33.8752037,151.2203043,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x6b12ae0d85210bd7:0x209717e75c98eb2c!8m2!3d-33.8752037!4d151.222493\" target=\"_blank\">Darlinghurst</a> only few meters away from the famous Coca Cola sign. 5 minutes walk from the king cross station.</p>",
