            "title" : "Request your tax back",
            "header" : "article-header-5b2da4d4ae86ed7f92ac88e1.jpeg",
            "header_by_html" : "<p><a href=\"https://unsplash.com/photos/p5x4IKEkWSo\" target=\"_blank\">@anniespratt</a> from Unsplash</p>",
            "header_by_markdown" : "[@anniespratt](https://unsplash.com/photos/p5x4IKEkWSo) from Unsplash",
            "content_html" : "<h3 id=\"whatisit\">What is it?</h3>\n<p>Every year in June the government is collecting taxes. In Australia you need to lodge your incomes with the government to claim your tax back. Two options are available, you can either go with a tax agent who cost around 10% of it. A simple Google search can help you with that. But you can also do it by yourself online, and that is what this article is about. One last thing to mention, you don't necessary end up with an excess of money, but it is usually the case.</p>\n<h3 id=\"startestimateyourrevenue\">Start &amp; estimate your revenue</h3>\n<p>To estimate your income the Australian Taxation Office (ATO) build the <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/Calculators-and-tools/Host/?anchor=IncomeTaxEstimator/questions&anchor=IncomeTaxEstimator&anchor=IncomeTaxEstimator/questions#IncomeTaxEstimator/questions\" target=\"_blank\">income tax estimator</a>. It will tell you know how much you can hope to received out of your tax back. All you will need is you payment summary from your employer, deliver each June. To access the ATO  website you need to register to myGov website. From there you will be able to link it with the ATP, we have a detailed process of that in <a href=\"/article/5b3f4de0eee0b11f5e8b6e74\" target=\"_blank\">this article</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"lodgeyouincomes\">Lodge you incomes</h3>\n<p>I've been quite surprise by how easy &amp; smooth was the tax-back online form. The first step is to check and update your contact information and bank details. Then fill up a set of questions. <code>You must know than for taxes purposes you are an Australian resident even if you are on a working or student visa</code>. The final step is to lodge you gross income. Your bank automatically lodge your interest to the ATO. Some company filled you gross income too. If not manually add your gross income with the online form. All the information you will need is written on your payment summary. Fill out the form without spaces or comma. Once done it usually takes less than 2 weeks to process your tax return and received the payment.</p>\n<h3 id=\"whatnext\">What next?</h3>\n<p>Well nothing really, check your bank account to make sure than you received the deposit. We will add a new article about what you can claim for your tax return on the future.</p>",
            "content_markdown" : "###What is it?\nEvery year in June the government is collecting taxes. In Australia you need to lodge your incomes with the government to claim your tax back. Two options are available, you can either go with a tax agent who cost around 10% of it. A simple Google search can help you with that. But you can also do it by yourself online, and that is what this article is about. One last thing to mention, you don't necessary end up with an excess of money, but it is usually the case.\n\n### Start & estimate your revenue\nTo estimate your income the Australian Taxation Office (ATO) build the [income tax estimator](https://www.ato.gov.au/Calculators-and-tools/Host/?anchor=IncomeTaxEstimator/questions&anchor=IncomeTaxEstimator&anchor=IncomeTaxEstimator/questions#IncomeTaxEstimator/questions). It will tell you know how much you can hope to received out of your tax back. All you will need is you payment summary from your employer, deliver each June. To access the ATO  website you need to register to myGov website. From there you will be able to link it with the ATP, we have a detailed process of that in [this article](/article/5b3f4de0eee0b11f5e8b6e74).\n\n### Lodge you incomes\nI've been quite surprise by how easy & smooth was the tax-back online form. The first step is to check and update your contact information and bank details. Then fill up a set of questions. `You must know than for taxes purposes you are an Australian resident even if you are on a working or student visa`. The final step is to lodge you gross income. Your bank automatically lodge your interest to the ATO. Some company filled you gross income too. If not manually add your gross income with the online form. All the information you will need is written on your payment summary. Fill out the form without spaces or comma. Once done it usually takes less than 2 weeks to process your tax return and received the payment.\n\n### What next?\nWell nothing really, check your bank account to make sure than you received the deposit. We will add a new article about what you can claim for your tax return on the future.",
            "short_content" : "Requesting your tax back is an essential step into your Australian settlement. It looks complicated, but in fact it can you can do it by yourself,  in less 30 minutes."
