            "title" : "Paramount recreation club",
            "content_html" : "<h3 id=\"ambiance\">Ambiance:</h3>\n<p>Paramount recreation club is a place to work out and to hang out and a little bit of both as they described it. The kiosk which is the name of the coffee is a medium size place, extending to an outside table and a rooftop terrace. The architecture of the space is quite modern and we really enjoyed sharing the outside concrete table, that was a good conversation starter. To see the full list of their activities have a look at their <a href=\"https://paramountrecreation.club/\" target=\"_blank\">website</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"cuisine\">Cuisine:</h3>\n<p>For what we seen the cuisine is healthy and looks good. We didn't had the chance to eat in, so we won't go further on commenting it, but we'll love to hear your feedback on it (check below). You can see their full choice on their menu.</p>\n<h3 id=\"pricing\">Pricing:</h3>\n<p>Interestingly enough most of the meal on the <a href=\"https://paramountrecreation.club/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/RecClub_Autumn_Menu_2018.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">menu</a> are $17. The cafe are $4.</p>\n<h3 id=\"service\">Service:</h3>\n<p>The personal where very welcoming and ready to serve us. We didn't have to wait too long even is the place was quite busy.</p>\n<h3 id=\"location\">Location:</h3>\n<p>The place is well situated between Museum station and Central only few minutes walk from both. For full details please check the <a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/80+Commonwealth+St,+Surry+Hills+NSW+2010/@-33.8793612,151.2105093,19z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x6b12ae17f7bed441:0xd61714523bea9557!8m2!3d-33.8793612!4d151.2110565\" target=\"_blank\">map</a>.</p>",
