            "header" : "article-header-5b31cf5a54e7f415b7538e1d.jpg",
            "short_content" : "Opal is the provider for transport New South wales. The opal card is needed to take any mode of public transportation in Sydney (train, bus, ferry, light rail).",
            "title" : "Opal",
            "content_html" : "<h3 id=\"generalnote\">General note:</h3>\n<p>The Sydney transport, are usually more expensive than other city around the world and unfortunately there is no monthly subscription. The price of your travel can go from $0 to $15 depending of your mode of transportation, the distance you are traveling and the time of the day. </p>\n<h3 id=\"howisitworking\">How is it working:</h3>\n<p>The Adult card can be obtained in most of the shop around Sydney, the card in itself is free but the minimum required is $10. The card can be recharged from kiosks is larges station across Sydney or from the opal website and mobile app. It usually takes 15 minutes from any payment from internet to go through. It is also possible to plan an automatic recharge of the card every time it's sold is below $10, thus from the mobile app or website.</p>\n<h3 id=\"thingstoknow\">Things to know:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Buses are cheaper than trains, but usually slower.</li>\n<li>Any transportation takes with less than an hour apart will be consider as transfer, and a $2 discount will be applied.</li>\n<li>After 8 travels your fare will be divided by 2.</li>\n<li>If the card is not tapped off the maximum fare will be applied</li>\n<li>On Sunday and public holiday the maximum fare is $2.7 per travel.</li>\n<li>The train to and from the airport is $15.</li>\n<li>The prices are 30% higher during pic hours.</li>\n<li>The fine for traveling without a ticket are fixed at $200</li>\n<li>The fine for putting your feet on the seat are fixed at $100 (but not enforced)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"opalmobileapp\">Opal mobile app:</h3>\n<p>The opal official mobile app is free and allow you to see your travel and their price, \"Top up\" (add money on your card), add auto Top Up. It also allows you to lock your card in case of lost of stolen property, the remaining funds can then be transferred to a new card. You can add manage more than one card for the other member of your family.</p>\n<h3 id=\"tripviewandtripviewlite\">TripView and TripView lite:</h3>\n<p>TripView allow you to have a real time view of every bus, train, ferry in Sydney. The paid version $5 will let you save your travel when the free version forces you to add the travel every time. The time for each transport is refreshed in real time in function of their real position, a map lets you visualize how far is the bus. The app will also let you know of any delay or incident even if it's hidden in a long list.</p>",
            "content_markdown" : "###General note:\nThe Sydney transport, are usually more expensive than other city around the world and unfortunately there is no monthly subscription. The price of your travel can go from $0 to $15 depending of your mode of transportation, the distance you are traveling and the time of the day. \n\n###How is it working:\nThe Adult card can be obtained in most of the shop around Sydney, the card in itself is free but the minimum required is $10. The card can be recharged from kiosks is larges station across Sydney or from the opal website and mobile app. It usually takes 15 minutes from any payment from internet to go through. It is also possible to plan an automatic recharge of the card every time it's sold is below $10, thus from the mobile app or website.\n\n###Things to know:\n - Buses are cheaper than trains, but usually slower.\n - Any transportation takes with less than an hour apart will be consider as transfer, and a $2 discount will be applied.\n - After 8 travels your fare will be divided by 2.\n - If the card is not tapped off the maximum fare will be applied\n - On Sunday and public holiday the maximum fare is $2.7 per travel.\n - The train to and from the airport is $15.\n - The prices are 30% higher during pic hours.\n - The fine for traveling without a ticket are fixed at $200\n - The fine for putting your feet on the seat are fixed at $100 (but not enforced)\n\n###Opal mobile app:\nThe opal official mobile app is free and allow you to see your travel and their price, \"Top up\" (add money on your card), add auto Top Up. It also allows you to lock your card in case of lost of stolen property, the remaining funds can then be transferred to a new card. You can add manage more than one card for the other member of your family.\n\n###TripView and TripView lite:\nTripView allow you to have a real time view of every bus, train, ferry in Sydney. The paid version $5 will let you save your travel when the free version forces you to add the travel every time. The time for each transport is refreshed in real time in function of their real position, a map lets you visualize how far is the bus. The app will also let you know of any delay or incident even if it's hidden in a long list.",
