        "_id" : "5b41fa93e3669e23cbbeffd4",
        "content" : {
            "header" : "article-header-5b41fa93e3669e23cbbeffd4.jpeg",
            "header_by_markdown" : "[@craftedbygc](https://unsplash.com/photos/s9CC2SKySJM) from Unsplash",
            "header_by_html" : "<p><a href=\"https://unsplash.com/photos/s9CC2SKySJM\" target=\"_blank\">@craftedbygc</a> from Unsplash</p>",
            "short_content" : "The tax file number (TFN) is a unique number provided by the Australian taxation office. The ATO use this number to manage and follow your personal income. You will need it to work in Australia and lodge your tax return.",
            "title" : "Taxe File Number",
            "content_html" : "<h3 id=\"whydoineedatfnwhen\">Why do I need a TFN &amp; when?</h3>\n<p>The TFN is a 10 digit number who differentiates you from any other worker in Australia. Your employer will use it for the sole purpose of assigning  your earning to the taxation office. You are required to have it before being able to do any kind of work. For these reasons it is recommended to do it as soon as you have a valid address. The all process of requesting your <code>TFN takes less than 5 minutes</code>. But you will usually wait <code>2 weeks before receiving it</code> by postal service.</p>\n<h3 id=\"wheretostart\">Where to start?</h3>\n<p>Before you start any procedure, you will need a valid Australian address. It is also recommended than you have a phone number, to be contacted if some information are missing. And finally you will need your password and a valid visa to you to work in Australia. To sum up:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Proof of identity (Passport)</li>\n<li>Valid address</li>\n<li>Phone number (within Australia)</li>\n<li>Valid Visa (with work right).\n</br></br>\nYou got it all? The next step is to visit the <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/individuals/tax-file-number/apply-for-a-tfn/foreign-passport-holders\" target=\"_blank\">ATO website</a> and fill up the form. It is fairly quick. We recommend to keep note of the application reference number, it might be needed in case of an issue. After a maximum of 28day (usually less than 14day) you will receive a letter with your TFN.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"whatnext\">What next</h3>\n<p>Keep your TFN document in a safe spot, you will need it for almost every other official action. Send it to yourself in Facebook, so you are sure to have it somewhere. Your TFN will stay available on your <a href=\"/article/5b3f4de0eee0b11f5e8b6e74\" target=\"_blank\">MyGov account</a>, but you will need it to create the account. The ATO also created a <a href=\"https://www.ato.gov.au/Individuals/Tax-file-number/Lost-or-stolen-TFN/\" target=\"_blank\">page</a> in case of you lost it.</p>",
            "content_markdown" : "###Why do I need a TFN & when?\nThe TFN is a 10 digit number who differentiates you from any other worker in Australia. Your employer will use it for the sole purpose of assigning  your earning to the taxation office. You are required to have it before being able to do any kind of work. For these reasons it is recommended to do it as soon as you have a valid address. The all process of requesting your `TFN takes less than 5 minutes`. But you will usually wait `2 weeks before receiving it` by postal service.\n\n### Where to start?\nBefore you start any procedure, you will need a valid Australian address. It is also recommended than you have a phone number, to be contacted if some information are missing. And finally you will need your password and a valid visa to you to work in Australia. To sum up:\n  - Proof of identity (Passport)\n  - Valid address\n  - Phone number (within Australia)\n  - Valid Visa (with work right).\n</br></br>\nYou got it all? The next step is to visit the [ATO website](https://www.ato.gov.au/individuals/tax-file-number/apply-for-a-tfn/foreign-passport-holders) and fill up the form. It is fairly quick. We recommend to keep note of the application reference number, it might be needed in case of an issue. After a maximum of 28day (usually less than 14day) you will receive a letter with your TFN.\n\n### What next\nKeep your TFN document in a safe spot, you will need it for almost every other official action. Send it to yourself in Facebook, so you are sure to have it somewhere. Your TFN will stay available on your [MyGov account](/article/5b3f4de0eee0b11f5e8b6e74), but you will need it to create the account. The ATO also created a [page](https://www.ato.gov.au/Individuals/Tax-file-number/Lost-or-stolen-TFN/) in case of you lost it."
        },
